props.description:
The maximum number of digits in the names of the frames, e.g. myAnim0001 has 4 digits.

 Format for data:
	{
		fps:30,
		labels:
		{
			animStart:0,
			animStart_loop:15
		},
		origin:{ x: 20, y:30 },
		frames:
		[
			{
				name:"myAnim#",
				min:1,
				max:20,
				digits:4
			}
		]
	}

The object describes a 30 fps animation that is 20 frames long, and was originally myAnim0001.png->myAnim0020.png,
with frame labels on the first and 16th frame. 'digits' is optional, and defaults to 4.
